bug.short_desc: Some fonts are missing on the netinst and dvd
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: On the page with language selection there are missing fonts for Tibetan, Khmer and Burmese. This happens only on netinst and dvd. Lives have fonts. There are only utf characters visible (please see the attachment).
There aren't many things translated in those languages, but for example in time and date user can't properly set time zone because of this bug (see second attachment).
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): anaconda-25.20-1 Fedora-Server-dvd-x86_64-25-Alpha-1.2.iso
How reproducible: always
Additional info: I propose this as final blocker as it violates the criterion: "The installer must correctly display all sufficiently complete translations available for use."
Created attachment 1193984 missing fonts in language selection
Created attachment 1193985 Missing fonts in time and date

Discussed during the 2016-08-29 blocker review meeting: [1]
The decision to classify this bug as an AcceptedBlocker was made because it is a clear violation of the following Final Blocker critiera:
"The installer must correctly display all sufficiently complete translations available for use."
[1] https://meetbot.fedoraproject.org/fedora-blocker-review/2016-08-29/f25-blocker-review.2016-08-29-16.00.txt
